52":"1252","1250":"1250","Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1252–":"about 1252–Deceased","1252–Female":"1252–Deceased","1250–Male":"1250–Deceased","1275–Male":"1275–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","ABT 1252":"about 1252","ABT 1275":"about 1275","1275":"1275","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","of Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"thornton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from any of numerous places throughout England and Scotland so called, from Old English <i>thorn</i> ‘thorn tree’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The placename is most frequent in northern England, especially Yorkshire, where there are at least 16 possible sources for the surname.","Irish: Anglicized (translated) form of Gaelic <b>Mac Sceacháin</b> ‘son of <i>Sceachán</i>’ (see   Skehan  ).","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Draighneáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Draighneán</i>’ (see   Drennan  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Thornber","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the five minor places in Yorkshire called Thornber, particularly Thornber in Halton West. The placenames derive from Old English <i>thorn</i> ‘thorn’ + <i>beorg</i> ‘hill, mound’.","Irish: adopted for various Irish names containing an element meaning ‘thorn’; compare   Thornton  ."]},{"name":"Thorton","meanings":["(1997: 465;2007: 2025; 2010: NA)","English: probably a shortened form of   Thornton  , or a habitational name from Thorton in Marnhull, Dorset, which has the same origin."]},{"name":"Skehan","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Sceacháin</b> or <b>Ó Sceacháin</b> ‘son (or descendant) of <i>Sceachán</i>’, a personal name probably based on a diminutive of <i>sceach</i> ‘briar, thorn bush’. The Gaelic name has sometimes been ‘translated’ as   Thornton  ."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary thornton was born about 1252, in Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir Piers Thornton. She had at least 1 son with Henry Donne."},"et":{"ABT 1252–":"umbes 1252–Surnud","1252–Female":"1252–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","ABT 1252":"umbes 1252","ABT 1275":"umbes 1275","1275":"1275","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1252–":"noin 1252–Kuollut","1252–Female":"1252–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","ABT 1252":"noin 1252","ABT 1275":"noin 1275","1275":"1275","1252":"1252","1250":"1250","Utkinton, Ches, Eng":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Utkinton